[0.000, "o", "                                                                                                                                              \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[1m\u001b[38;2;224;222;244m1. The New Productivity Bottleneck: Information Discovery\u001b[39m\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                                                          \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mThe primary source of friction for engineering teams has shifted. While technical debt was once the top concern, the \u001b[1mAtlassian State of Developer Experience 2025\u001b[22m report indicates that \u001b[1mfinding information\u001b[22m is now the #1 \"time\u001b[39m    \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244msuck.\"\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                                                             \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m"]
[0.000, "o", "█\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m*\u001b[39m \u001b[1m\u001b[38;2;224;222;244mArticle Angle:\u001b[22m Coding agents aren't just for writing functions; their greatest productivity impact may be as intelligent retrieval layers that solve the information discovery problem, allowing developers to bypass the\u001b[39m       \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n     \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mfriction of navigating fragmented documentation and legacy codebases.\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                           \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n                                                                                                                                                                          "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                           \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[1m\u001b[38;2;224;222;244m2. Agents as Standardization Engines\u001b[39m\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                                                                               \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mYour notes on \"core concepts\" highlight that agents provide:\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                       \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[1mDomain Expertise:\u001b[22m Specialized agents (Go, Security, DevOps) provide deep knowledge on demand.\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                   \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[1mTeam Standardization:\u001b[22m Using a \"senior reviewer\" age"]
[0.000, "o", "nt ensures that every developer—regardless of experience—is measured against the same standards and best practices.\u001b[39m                                                          \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[1mConsistent Voice:\u001b[22m Reducing the cognitive load of switching between different styles or behavioral constraints.\u001b[39m                                                                                                                  \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[1m\u001b[38;2;224;2"]
[0.000, "o", "22;244m3. Controlling Complexity with Domain-Driven Design (DDD)\u001b[39m\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                                                          \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mThe complexity of modern software is still the greatest hurdle. As highlighted in your \u001b[3mDomain-Driven Design\u001b[23m notes:\u001b[39m                                                                                                                 \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[1mLeverage through Models:\u001b[22m LLMs can help developers brainstorm\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                    \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n                                                                                                                                                                                  "]
