[0.000, "o", "                                                                                                                                           \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[1m\u001b[38;2;224;222;244m2. Agents as Standardization Engines\u001b[39m\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                                                                               \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mYour notes on \"core concepts\" highlight that agents provide:\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                       \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[1mDomain Expertise:\u001b[22m Specialized agents (Go, Security, DevOps) provide deep knowledge on demand.\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                   \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b"]
[0.000, "o", "[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[1mTeam Standardization:\u001b[22m Using a \"senior reviewer\" agent ensures that every developer—regardless of experience—is measured against the same standards and best practices.\u001b[39m                                                          \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[1mConsistent Voice:\u001b[22m Reducing the cognitive load of switching between different styles or behavioral constraints.\u001b[39m                                                                                                                  \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n                                                                                                                                                                                                 "]
[0.000, "o", "                                    \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[1m\u001b[38;2;224;222;244m3. Controlling Complexity with Domain-Driven Design (DDD)\u001b[39m\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                                                          \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mThe complexity of modern software is still the greatest hurdle. As highlighted in your \u001b[3mDomain-Driven Design\u001b[23m notes:\u001b[39m                                                                                                                 \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[1mLeverage through Models:\u001b[22m LLMs can help developers brainstorm and experiment with domain models more rapidly.\u001b[39m                                                                                                                    \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m*\u001b[39m \u001b[1m\u001b[38;2;224;222;244mConscious Knowledge Growth:\u001b[22m Highly produc"]
[0.000, "o", "tive teams grow their knowledge consciously. Agents can act as the \"memory\" of a team, distilling brainstorming sessions into a \"knowledge-rich model\" that binds the domain to the\u001b[39m    \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n     \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mcode.\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                                                           \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[1m\u001b[38;2;224;222;"]
[0.000, "o", "244m4. Measuring What\u001b[39m\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                                                                                                  \u001b[38;2;69;71;90m█\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[9B\u001b[52;4H\u001b[?2026l"]
