[0.000, "o", "9m\u001b[22m \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m{\"query\":\"developer productivity in the age of large language models and coding agents\"}\u001b[39m                                                                                       \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[2m---\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mFile: Readwise/Articles/Fixing Engineering’s Biggest Time Suck Finding Information.md\u001b[39m                                                                          "]
[0.001, "o", "                                                                   \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mRelevance: 1.1001073122024536\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mContent: ## Highlights\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                                            \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- [[2025-07-24]] The leading cause of friction and time waste for engineering teams is not tech debt, testing or code reviews, but finding information.\u001b[39m                                                                          \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;"]
[0.000, "o", "110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m  This unexpected but revealing insight comes from Atlassian’s “State of Developer Experience 2025\u001b[38;2;235;111;146m (https://www.atlassian.com/teams/software-development/state-of-developer-experience-2025)\u001b[38;2;224;222;244m” report. Finding information has\u001b[39m     \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244movertaken technical debt\u001b[38;2;235;111;146m (https://thenewstack.io/how-frontend-devs-can-take-technical-debt-out-of-code/)\u001b[38;2;224;222;244m, which topped the list last year, as the top source of developer friction.\u001b[39m                                               \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[2m---\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[2m---\u001b[22m   "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                                                                                                                                                                            \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mFile: working/idx_team/Initial DevSat Survey.md\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mRelevance: 1.2507269382476807\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mContent: # Developer Satisfaction Survey\u001b[39m                                                                     "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                                                                     \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[2m---\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[2m---\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mFile: working/aix/blueprint/core-concepts-outline.md\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                              \u001b[38;2;110;106;1"]
[0.000, "o", "34m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mRelevance: 1.2536908388137817\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mContent: Use agents when you need:\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                                \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- \u001b[1mConsistent personality\u001b[22m: Same \"voice\" across conversations\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                      \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- \u001b[1mDomain expertise\u001b[22m: Deep"]
[0.000, "o", " knowledge in a specific area (Go, security, DevOps)\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- \u001b[1mBehavioral constraints\u001b[22m: Enforce specific workflows or outputs\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                  \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- \u001b[1mTeam standardization\u001b[22m: Everyone uses the same \"senior reviewer\" agent\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                           \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[2m---\u001b[22m                                                                                                                     "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                                                          \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[2m---\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mFile: Readwise/Books/Domain-Driven Design.md\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                      \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mRelevance: 1.2559380531311035\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[38;2;110;1"]
[0.000, "o", "06;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mContent: ## Highlights\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                                            \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- [[2021-08-03]] The key to controlling complexity is a good domain model, a model that goes beyond a surface vision of a domain by introducing an underlying structure, which gives the software developers the leverage they\u001b[39m   \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m    \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mneed. A good domain model can be incredibly valuable, but it’s not something that’s easy to make. Few people can do it well, and it’s very hard to teach.\u001b[39m                                                                      \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m      \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- Note: How many of my softw"]
[0.000, "o", "are projects have failed over the years from the lack of having a domain model or even a lack of understanding the domain at all?\u001b[39m                                                                \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- [[2021-08-03]] Every software program relates to some activity or interest of its user. That subject area to which the user applies the program is the domain of the software.\u001b[39m                                                 \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- [[2021-08-03]] A model is a selectively simplified and consciously structured form of knowledge. An appropriate model makes sense of information and focuses it on a problem.\u001b[39m                                                  \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- [[2021-08-03]] A domain model is not a particular diagram; it is the idea that the diagram is intended to convey.\u001b[39m               "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                                               \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- [[2021-08-03]] It is the creativity of brainstorming and massive experimentation, leveraged through a model-based language and disciplined by the feedback loop through implementation, that makes it possible to find a\u001b[39m       \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m    \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mknowledge-rich model and distill it.\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                           \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m      \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- Note: One thing that I need to improve upon is these types of brainstorming sessions. This also comes down to my lack of ability to focus in most meetings.,\u001b[39m                                                               \u001b[38;2;1"]
[0.000, "o", "10;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- [[2021-08-03]] Highly productive teams grow their knowledge consciously, practicing continuous learning (Kerievsky 2003). For developers, this means improving technical knowledge, along with general domain-modeling skills\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m    \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m(such as those in this book). But it also includes serious learning about the specific domain they are working in.\u001b[39m                                                                                                             \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m      \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- Note: Highly productive teams also practice DevOps. How do I become interested enough in the business to want to become intimate with the domain?\u001b[39m                                                                          \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- [[2021-08-03]] Policy is another"]
[0.000, "o", " name for the design pattern known as STRATEGY (Gamma et al. 1995). It is usually motivated by the need to substitute different rules, which is not needed here, as far as we know.\u001b[39m            \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- [[2021-08-03]] A domain model can be the core of a common language for a software project. The model is a set of concepts built up in the heads of people on the project, with terms and relationships that reflect domain\u001b[39m     \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m    \u001b[38;2;224;222;244minsight. These terms and interrelationships provide the semantics of a language that is tailored to the domain while being precise enough for technical development. This is a crucial cord that weaves the model into\u001b[39m         \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m    \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mdevelopment activity and binds it with the code.\u001b[39m                                                                                  "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                                             \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- [[2021-08-03]] The Language Instinct, by Steven Pinker\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                         \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- [[2021-08-03]] If sophisticated domain experts don’t understand the model, there is something wrong with the model.\u001b[39m                                                                                                            \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- [[2021-08-03]] The essential principle is that any element of a layer depends only on other elements in the same layer or on elements of the layers “beneath” it. Communication upward must pass through some indirect\u001b[39m         \u001b[38"]
[0.000, "o", ";2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m    \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mmechanism,\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m-\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m[[2021-08-03]] An object defined primarily by its identity is called an ENTITY.1 ENTITIES have special modeling and design considerations. They have life cycles that can radically change their form and content, but a\u001b[39m       \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m    \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mthread of continuity must be maintained.\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                       \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m-\u001b[39m"]
[0.000, "o", " \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m[[2021-08-03]] An object that represents a descriptive aspect of the domain with no conceptual identity is called a VALUE OBJECT. VALUE OBJECTS are instantiated to represent elements of the design that we care about only\u001b[39m   \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m    \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mfor what they are, not who or which they are.\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                  \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m-\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m[[2021-08-03]] A SERVICE is an operation offered as an interface that stands alone in the model, without encapsulating state, as ENTITIES and VALUE OBJECTS do. SERVICES are a common pattern in technical frameworks, but\u001b[39m     \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m    \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mthey can also apply in the domain layer.\u001b[39m              "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                                                                                                                                         \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m- [[2021-08-03]] A good SERVICE has three characteristics. 1. The operation relates to a domain concept that is not a natural part of an ENTITY or VALUE OBJECT. 2. The interface is defined in terms of other elements of the\u001b[39m   \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m    \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mdomain model. 3. The operation is stateless.\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                   \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[2m---\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                                                            "]
[0.000, "o", "                                                   \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[2m---\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mFile: working/idx_team/Reading List.md\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                            \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mRelevance: 1.2762482166290283\u001b[39m                                                                                                                                                                                                     \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;224"]
[0.000, "o", ";222;244mContent: - \u001b[3mThe Why:\u001b[23m The science of delivery. It provides the evidence for which metrics (DORA) actually move the needle for developer velocity.\u001b[39m                                                                                   \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m \u001b[2m---\u001b[22m                                                                                                                                                                                                                               \u001b[38;2;110;106;134m│\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;110;106;134m╰────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────"]
[0.000, "o", "───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[38;2;196;167;231m✦ \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mBased on your notes, here is a synthesized framework for your article on developer productivity in the age of LLMs and coding agents:\u001b[39m\r\n\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1m\u001b[38;2;224;222;244m1. The New Productivity Bottleneck: Information Discovery\u001b[39m\u001b[22m\r\n  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mThe primary source of friction for engineering teams has shifted. While technical debt was once the top concern, the \u001b[1mAtlassian State of Developer Experience 2025\u001b[22m report indicates that \u001b[1mfinding information\u001b[22m is now the #1 \"time\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244msuck.\"\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m*\u001b[39m \u001b[1m\u001b[38;2;224;222;244mArticle Angle:\u001b[22m Coding agents aren't just for writing functions; their greatest productivity impact may be as intelligent retr"]
[0.000, "o", "ieval layers that solve the information discovery problem, allowing developers to bypass the\u001b[39m\r\n     \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mfriction of navigating fragmented documentation and legacy codebases.\u001b[39m\r\n\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1m\u001b[38;2;224;222;244m2. Agents as Standardization Engines\u001b[39m\u001b[22m\r\n  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mYour notes on \"core concepts\" highlight that agents provide:\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[1mDomain Expertise:\u001b[22m Specialized agents (Go, Security, DevOps) provide deep knowledge on demand.\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[1mTeam Standardization:\u001b[22m Using a \"senior reviewer\" agent ensures that every developer—regardless of experience—is measured against the same standards and best practices.\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[1mConsistent Voice:\u001b[22m Reducing the cognitive load of switching between different styles or behavioral constraints.\u001b[39m\r\n\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1m\u001b[38;2;224;222;244m3. Controlling Complexity with Domain-Driven Design (DDD)\u001b[39m\u001b[22m\r\n  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mThe complexity of modern software is still the g"]
[0.000, "o", "reatest hurdle. As highlighted in your \u001b[3mDomain-Driven Design\u001b[23m notes:\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[1mLeverage through Models:\u001b[22m LLMs can help developers brainstorm and experiment with domain models more rapidly.\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m*\u001b[39m \u001b[1m\u001b[38;2;224;222;244mConscious Knowledge Growth:\u001b[22m Highly productive teams grow their knowledge consciously. Agents can act as the \"memory\" of a team, distilling brainstorming sessions into a \"knowledge-rich model\" that binds the domain to the\u001b[39m\r\n     \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mcode.\u001b[39m\r\n\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1m\u001b[38;2;224;222;244m4. Measuring What Matters (DORA Metrics)\u001b[39m\u001b[22m\r\n  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mTo move beyond hype, productivity must be grounded in the \"science of delivery.\"\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[1mArticle Angle:\u001b[22m Use DORA metrics (from \u001b[3mThe Why\u001b[23m) to evaluate if AI tools are actually moving the needle on velocity and stability, rather than just increasing the volume of code produced.\u001b[39m\r\n\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1m\u001b[38;2;224;222;244m5. The Evolution of th"]
[0.000, "o", "e Developer Role\u001b[39m\u001b[22m\r\n  \u001b[38;2;224;222;244mProductivity in this age is less about \"typing speed\" and more about:\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[1mContinuous Learning:\u001b[22m Developers must shift focus toward becoming \"intimate with the business domain.\"\u001b[39m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[1mBrainstorming and Experimentation:\u001b[22m Using agents to leverage \"massive experimentation\" (as noted in the DDD highlights) to find the right architectural patterns.\u001b[39m\r\n\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1m\u001b[38;2;224;222;244mPotential Article Titles:\u001b[39m\u001b[22m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[3mFrom Tech Debt to Information Friction: How Agents are Rewriting the Productivity Playbook\u001b[39m\u001b[23m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[3mThe Senior Reviewer in the Machine: Standardizing Engineering Teams with AI\u001b[39m\u001b[23m\r\n   \u001b[38;2;224;222;244m* \u001b[3mModel-Driven Development in the Age of Agents: Using LLMs to Conquer Complexity\u001b[39m\u001b[23m\r\n\r\n\u001b[48;2;32;30;44m\u001b[38;2;25;23;36m▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀▀"]
